<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-09 15:00:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jerry West Says Shaq Wil Win MVP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Jerry West has made a bold  
prediction. 
</P>
<P>
	``Shaquille O'Neal will be the MVP this season,'' said West, the  
executive vice president of the Los Angeles Lakers. ``There has 
been tremendous enthusiasm on his part and he is the happiest I 
have seen him since he has been in Los Angeles. He believes in what 
(coach Phil Jackson) is trying to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	West made his comments Saturday while speaking to the media for  
the first time this season. 
</P>
<P>
	The 7-foot-1 center wasn't worried about personal accolades, but  
rather the team's success. 
</P>
<P>
	``It doesn't matter (what West said),'' said O'Neal. ``How does  
that work anyway? (The media) votes me in, right? Most of you don't 
like me anyway. It's all about the jewelry, I just want a 
championship.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson saw the prediction as a confidence booster for O'Neal.  
</P>
<P>
	``It is a nice sentiment,'' said Jackson. ``He should be among  
the top five vote-getters in the MVP, he has the ability to do 
that. He has to stay healthy though.'' 
</P>
<P>
	West is not only impressed with O'Neal, but also the enthusiasm  
that the whole squad has shown for Jackson's ``triangle'' offense. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have been impressed with the tremendous concentration that  
our players are showing out there and also the fact that they have 
worked so hard considering how strenuous the camp has been,'' he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Glen Rice, a free agent at the end of the season, was also on  
the mind of West, who considers Rice to be in the best shape of his 
career. Rice has tendinitis in his left knee, which has sidelined 
him for one practice and part of the team's scrimmage Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``Glen is going to have a great year, not a good year,'' said  
West. ``Physically, with the exception of his tendinitis, he looks 
great. He is going to have lots of opportunities to score.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson held his first intersquad scrimmage Friday night,  
bringing in officials to put a gauge on where his team stands at 
this point. His first team was comprised of O'Neal, Kobe Bryant, 
Derek Fisher, Rice and A.C. Green. Rick Fox filled in for Rice 
later in the scrimmage. 
</P>
<P>
	``The first team had a lot of fun. Some of the other guys  
struggled. I was real impressed we got through five games. It let 
the horse out of the barn, it was fun for them,'' Jackson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson also was impressed with this rookie squad, which  
includes No. 1 draft pick Devean George and free agent Gerald 
Jordan, who outplayed the Lakers' second team of veterans. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
