<HEADLINE> 2003 Skating Championship in Dallas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) -- Dallas was selected on Saturday  
as the site for the 2003 U.S. Figure Skating Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States Figure Skating Association said Dallas beat  
out bids from Minneapolis and St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	The event, which has never been held in Texas, is expected to  
bring more than 1,500 athletes, coaches and officials to Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
	The competition will be held mainly at American Airlines Center,  
a 20,000-seat facility scheduled to be completed in 2001. 
  	   	
