<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-09 15:40:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Silver Season Wins Again at Calder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Silver Season, who won the $200,000 Carry Stakes at  
Calder Race Course last July, had another big payday at the same 
track Saturday with a come-from-behind victory in the $300,000 
Smile Sprint Handicap for 3-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
	Rallying from next-to-last, Silver Season got through on the  
inside to win by 1 3/4 lengths over Son of a Pistol. Favored My Jeff's 
Mombo was third in a field of seven that went six furlongs. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver Season, ridden by Eibar Coa, was timed in 1:10 and paid  
$7.20, $3.80 and $2.40. Son of a Pistol paid $3.80 and $2.60, while 
My Jeff's Mombo paid $2.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Coa kept Silver Season on the rail down the backstretch as High  
Security set the pace. My Jeff's Mombo moved into second going to 
the far turn and Son of a Pistol was third. Silver Season was 
sixth, but in good position, four lengths off the pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The field bunched on the stretch turn. Silver Season came off  
the rail just long enough to drive between High Security and My 
Jeff's Mombo. He got the lead approaching the eighth pole and 
maintained a safe margin to the wire. 
</P>
<P>
	Son of a Pistol closed well for second, 1 1/2 lengths over a  
faltering My Jeff's Mombo. The favorite barely lasted for third, a 
nose in front of Thrillin Discovery. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver Season is the Kentucky-bred son of Silver Ghost owned by  
Buckram Oak Farm. He has won four of 14 starts and $387,469. After 
winning the Carry Stakes, he finished third in the Grade III 
Amsterdam at Saratoga and was soundly beaten in the Grade I King's 
Bishop. 
</P>
<P>
	Coa has ridden Silver Season in all four of his victories this  
year, but in only one of his seven losses as a 3-year-old, a 
third-place finish in the Grade II Riva Ridge at Belmont in June. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
