<HEADLINE> European stocks close mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks closed mixed Friday, with oil  
stocks slipping the most as prices fell and telecommunications 
shares rising on talk of consolidation. 
</P>
<P>
	BP Amoco fell 18.5 pence to close at 540 pence, and Shell lost  
15.5 pence to end at 441 pence. The drop was prompted by increased 
OPEC output and a rise in U.S. crude oil inventories pushing down 
prices. 
</P>
<P>
	Vodafone AirTouch, meanwhile, was one of the best performing  
shares in Europe, helped by news that it has boosted its 
shareholdings in several Japanese mobile telephone companies. The 
stock rose 10 pence, or 3.4 percent, to close at 303.25 pence. 
</P>
<P>
	MCI WorldCom's bid for Sprint earlier in the week has increased  
speculation that more deals are to come, prompting gains in the 
European telecoms sector. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 614 European companies rose 0.80  
points, or 0.3 percent, to close at 312.37. The worst performing 
index was energy, with a drop of 2.4 percent, followed by 
chemicals, which lost 1.0 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 310 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed down 0.56 points 
at 327.22. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 0.92 of a point to  
3884.32, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 18.18 points at 
3757.11. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, London's FTSE 100 index of blue-chip shares  
closed with a loss of 1.0 point to 6199.4. The Paris CAC-40 index 
fell 0.4 percent to 4,721.93, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index lost 0.5 
of a point to 5,419.26, Amsterdam's AEX index fell 0.2 percent to 
554.84 and Milan's MIBtel index fell 0.4 percent to 33,903. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
