<HEADLINE> Immigrant Ship Sinks Near Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- A boat filled with illegal Chinese  
immigrants sank Saturday off the Guatemalan coast. Five were killed 
and 38 were rescued, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The shipwreck occurred in the Pacific Ocean off Chiquimulia, 70  
miles south of Guatemala City. The boat sank during bad weather, 
Guatemalan immigration spokeswoman Sonia Ortiz said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear where the boat was coming from, but Ortiz said it  
was believed the immigrants were headed to Mexico and planned to 
continue by land from there to the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	Two of those rescued were treated for injuries.  
</P>
<P>
	Ortiz said the survivors would be deported.  
  	   	
</P>
