<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-09 12:28:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gateway Recalls Foam `Stress' Cows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Computer manufacturer Gateway Inc. is  
recalling about 1 million foam rubber ``stress'' cows due to 
choking hazard, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gateway has received three reports about pieces of the foam  
tearing away, posing a serious choking hazard to young children, 
the commission said. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no reports of injuries.  
</P>
<P>
	The foam cows are white with black spots, 4 1/2 inches long and 3  
inches high. The cow is supposed to relieve stress when squeezed 
repeatedly. 
</P>
<P>
	The Gateway logo rubber cow was a giveaway with a computer  
purchase from September 1997 to September 1999. A few were sold for 
about $4 during that time. 
</P>
<P>
	The commission recommends that customers throw away the cow, or  
visit any Gateway store for an exchange. For more information, 
customers should call 1-877-206-4889. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
