<HEADLINE> Ex-Vikings Executive Skoglund Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORONO, Minn. (AP) -- Former Minnesota Vikings chairman John  
Skoglund has died of lung cancer. He was 67. 
</P>
<P>
	Skoglund died Friday at his home in Orono. He was chairman of  
the Vikings' board until the team was sold last year to Red 
McCombs. His father, insurance mogul H.P. Skoglund, was one of the 
original owners of the Vikings. 
</P>
<P>
	As chairman, John Skoglund stayed out of the limelight. He said  
earlier this year that the satisfaction of owning part of the 
Vikings was enough for him. 
</P>
<P>
	His survivors include his wife, Adelaide.  
  	   	
</P>
