<HEADLINE> Delta Sells Stock in SAirGroup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Delta Air Lines has sold its 525,000 shares of  
stock in SAirGroup, the parent company of Swissair. 
</P>
<P>
	The transaction will result in a before-tax gain of about $29  
million and cash proceeds of about $114 million, the Atlanta-based 
airlines said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Delta's shares in SAirGroup amounted to about a 5 percent stake  
in the Swiss company. Delta had held the stock since 1989. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, Delta sold its 35.2 million shares of Singapore  
Airlines stock and repurchased 5 million shares of Delta stock held 
by Singapore. That sale came after Swissair pulled out of a 
three-way alliance with Delta and Singapore and sold its 8 million 
shares of Singapore stock. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
