<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Playboy Mansion Neighbors Complain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Hugh Hefner's neighbors say he has gone from  
Playboy to bad boy and they've had it with the traffic and 
screeching cars. 
</P>
<P>
	Holmby Hills residents living around the Playboy Mansion say  
their street is clogged with cars every time Hefner throws one of 
his notoriously extravagant parties. His mansion only has parking 
for 25. 
</P>
<P>
	``They come roaring down the hill and screech their brakes and  
stop and then roar off,'' said Howard Weinberger, 83. 
</P>
<P>
	A small group of neighbors has been trying for two years to get  
the city to add parking restrictions on the weekends. Last week, 
they were shut down again, but the City Council promised to look 
for a solution. 
</P>
<P>
	Bill Farley, a spokesman for Playboy Enterprises International  
Inc., said, ``If the restrictions go up, we'll live with them. We 
want to be a good neighbor.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
