<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Kentucky Starter Streck Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Former University of Kentucky football  
player Jeremy Streck, a starting senior guard last season, died 
Saturday of injuries suffered after being hit by a car. He was 23. 
</P>
<P>
	Streck had been in critical condition at the Ohio State Medical  
Center in Columbus since he was struck on Oct. 1. He was pronounced 
dead at 12:05 a.m. Saturday, said Ken Phillips, hospital 
administration manager. 
</P>
<P>
	Shortly after the accident, police charged Paul K. Synadinos,  
20, of Gahanna, Ohio, with DUI. There was no immediate word whether 
further charges would be filed against Synadinos. 
</P>
<P>
	A 6-foot-5, 313-pound lineman from Cincinnati, Streck started 18  
games and played in 32 during his career at Kentucky. He started 
all 12 games last season at left guard as the Wildcats went 7-5, 
making their first appearance in a New Year's Day bowl game since 
1952. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
