<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chilukki Wins $200K Oak Leaf Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Unbeaten Chilukki pulled away to win  
Saturday's $200,000 Oak Leaf Stakes at Santa Anita by 1 1/4 lengths 
over Abby Girl. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory in the race for 2-year-old fillies was Chilukki's  
first beyond a sprinting distance, and made her the probable 
favorite in the $1 million Breeders' Cup Juvenile Fillies race on 
Nov. 6 at Gulfstream Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by David Flores, Chilukki, the 1-2 favorite, covered 1  
mile in the stakes-record time of 1:36 in winning her sixth 
straight race, and paid $3, $2.40 and $2.10. The $120,000 winner's 
share increased her career earnings to $562,723. 
</P>
<P>
	``I love the way she relaxed today,'' trainer Bob Baffert said  
of the daughter of Cherokee Run. ``She does not need the lead. 
She's just professional, just so gifted.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chilukki had to wait out a stewards' inquiry before the result  
was made official. The stewards noted Chilukki drifted in nearing 
the finish line, causing Abby Girl and jockey Chris McCarron to 
steady momentarily. However, they ruled the incident had no bearing 
on the order of finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Abby Girl, who won her previous two starts, crossed the finish  
line 4 1/4 lengths in front of Spain and returned $3.20 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Spain, ridden by Gary Stevens, was a half-length ahead of Crown  
Of Crimson at the wire and paid $2.10 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	She's Classy finished fifth and last in the 31st running of the  
race. Each of the five entries carried 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The race was run at 1 1-16 miles before 1997, when Vivid Angel  
won in 1:37 1-5. Excellent Meeting won last year in 1:37 3-5. 
</P>
<P>
	A field of six, headed by Forest Camp and Dixie Union, is  
entered in Sunday's $200,000 Norfolk Stakes, a 1-mile race for 
2-year-olds. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
