<DOCNO> APW19991009.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-09 09:30:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Piazza To Miss Saturday's Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- All-Star catcher Mike Piazza was out of the New  
York Mets' lineup for a second straight day with an injured left 
thumb. 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza, who missed Game 3 of the New York Mets series against  
the Arizona Diamondbacks, was possibly available for pinch-hitting 
duties today. 
</P>
<P>
	``He is a little better,'' manager Bobby Valentine said before  
the game. ``He might be able to pinch-hit if all the treatment 
kicks in. It is still swollen.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza was icing his thumb before the game. He initially injured  
it Sept. 17 when he was hit by a foul ball against Philadelphia and 
re-aggravated it Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	X-rays of the thumb were negative but Piazza had a bad reaction  
to a cortisone shot. 
</P>
<P>
	Todd Pratt, who went 1-for-3 with two walks in Game 3, started  
once again in Piazza's place. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
