<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Arizona 31, No. 22 S. Calif. 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
                          *AP Sports Wrtier    	
</P>
<P>
	TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Trung Canidate ran for 194 yards and a  
touchdown and Arizona offset its woeful kicking game with strong 
defense to defeat No. 22 Southern Cal 31-24 Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wildcats (4-2, 2-1 Pac-10) had three of their seven sacks,  
an interception and scored on Kelvin Hunter's 24-yard fumble return 
after Canidate broke a 17-17 tie with an 11-yard TD run with 11:52 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	The Trojans (3-2, 1-2 Pac-10) also had a defensive touchdown -- a  
44-yard fumble return by Antuan Simmons early in the second quarter 
-- and Mike Van Raaphorst threw TD passes of 18 yards to Windrell 
Hayes and 21 yards to Marcell Allmond. 
</P>
<P>
	But Allmond's score came with 28 seconds remaining. When the  
ensuing onside kick went out of bounds, Southern Cal's three-game 
winning streak against Arizona was over. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier, Keith Smith ran 57 yards for a TD and threw a 17-yard  
pass to Dennis Northcutt for another, directing an Arizona offense 
that gained 550 yards against an opponent that led the conference 
in every defensive category. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona's Mark McDonald had a 43-yard field goal, but missed two  
others to go 1-for-9 on the season. 
</P>
<P>
	His field goal in the second quarter was Arizona's first in six  
games, and gave the Wildcats a 10-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	David Newbury tied it with a 40-yard field goal just before  
halftime. 
</P>
<P>
	Marcus Bell intercepted Van Raaphorst with 10:49 left in the  
game, and the Wildcats marched within range of McDonald's second 
miss -- from 43 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	The Trojans got the ball back with 9:21 remaining. But Joe  
Tafoya and Idris Haroon sacked Van Raaphorst on two of the next 
three snaps, and Southern Cal punted. 
</P>
<P>
	After an Arizona punt, Van Raaphorst tried to rally his team  
once more. 
</P>
<P>
	This time, he was denied by Northcutt, Arizona's career  
receiving leader, who stepped in at cornerback to control Hayes. 
</P>
<P>
	Van Raaphorst threw two incompletions, a running play gained  
seven yards and Van Raaphorst fumbled the fourth-down snap. The 
ball was kicked around and wound up in Hunter's hands for the 
clinching TD. 
</P>
<P>
	The Trojans exceeded their first-half production when they  
marched 79 yards with the opening kickoff of the second half, and 
Hayes' scoring reception sent them to a 17-10 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wildcats tied it again on a 17-yard pass from Smith to  
Northcutt with 41 seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona needed only four plays to cover 95 yards for its first  
TD. Smith covered the final 57 yards on a draw 4:40 into the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith gained 22 yards on his next carry, but McDonald missed a  
41-yard field goal at the end. 
</P>
<P>
	Southern Cal linebacker Zeke Moreno, who scored on a fumble  
return and an interception return in a win over Oregon State last 
week, figured in his third defensive score in two games. He sacked 
Smith for 14 yards and caused him to fumble, and Simmons got the 
ball in the open and scored 52 seconds into the second quarter. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
