<HEADLINE> Buffy's Angel Called a Throwback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- David Boreanaz may be among the hottest hunks of  
the new television season as the 244-year-old vampire ``Angel,'' 
but his charm is vintage 1950s. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's like a rugged, old-fashioned movie star. If this was the  
'50s, he might have changed his name to Rock,'' says 20th Century 
Fox Television senior vice president Marcia Shulman in the November 
issue of Cosmopolitan magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	Even Boreanaz' favorite movie is a throwback to the past: ``A  
Streetcar Named Desire.'' ``There's such grittiness and angst and 
passion and love and heat'' in it, he says. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's bigger than life, cooler than cooler,'' says Joss Whedon,  
creator of ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer'' and its new spinoff 
``Angel.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He says he was sold on Boreanaz by teen-agelike reaction of the  
show's female producer and casting director: ``They were grabbing 
me and screaming, 'Cast him!''' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
